Rating: 4
A friend brought this recipe to a book club meeting and I LOVED it so I made this twice in recent weeks. Because I really don't cook (lucky me, my husband does,) The First time I improvised and forgot to balance out the herbs, cheese and oil needed to flavor all the extras I added. There were too many vegetables tomatoes, celery slices, and snowpeas. I added imitation crab as well, but again it was dry, bland, and wasn't the right balance. Tonight I made it for a 4th of July party and it was FABULOUS! I did things differently. I added about six 3-inch long tops of asparagus that I drizzled in lots of olive oil topped it with some sea salt with a 1 minute microwaving, 20- 25 Kalamata olives cut into quarters, an extra cup of cheese (more Feta than goat,) 20-25 cut cherry tomatoes, and for a FABULOUS CRUNCH,I chopped nearly a whole bag of packaged mung bean sprouts and about 10 snowpeas chopped into 3rds. It was colorful and absolutely YUMMO! Next time I make it, I will try the total Mediterranean approach with sliced red onions, Kalamata olives, Gorgonzola and Motz cheese and basil with tomatoes. I will likely add some tuna packed in oil for some protein.

